{"ts":"2026-06-26T08:44:42.795Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Confirming Tailwind Hover Behavior**\n\nI've confirmed the unexpected hover behavior. It turns out that applying `group-hover` to the same element as the `group` class doesn't trigger the hover effect. The issue stems from Tailwind's generation of descendant combinator rules, which require the `group-hover` styles to be applied to a child or descendant of the `group` element. I've verified this with the actual generated CSS and now need to see where this behavior exists in our code.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
